20to%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20HB3%2C%20was%20signed%20by%20Florida%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20on%20Monday.%20It%20prohibits%20children%20under%2014%20from%20being%20on%20social%20media.%20Children%20ages%2014%20and%2015%20need%20their%20parent's%20consent%20to%20join%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Florida%20Gov.%20argued%20pedophiles%20are%20taking%20advantage%20of%20children%20on%20the%20apps.%20The%20Speaker%20of%20the%20Florida%20House%2C%20Paul%20Renner%2C%20echoed%20those%20concerns%20and%20also%20brought%20up%20mental%20health%20concerns%20associated%20with%20the%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20have%20a%20kid%20in%20the%20house%20safe%20seemingly%20and%20then%20you%20have%20predators%20that%20can%20get%20right%20in%20there%20into%20your%20own%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20DeSantis%20said%20at%20the%20bill%20signing%20ceremony.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20be%20doing%20everything%20right%2C%20but%20they%20know%20how%20to%20manipulate%20these%20different%20platforms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20requires%20social%20media%20companies%20to%20delete%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-you-must-be-13-facebook-instagram-problematic-law-coppa-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexisting%20accounts%20that%20belong%20to%20children%20under%2014%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20child's%20request%20within%20five%20business%20days%2C%20or%20a%20parent's%20request%20within%2010%20business%20days.%20For%2014%20or%2015-year-old%20children%2C%20the%20account%20must%20be%20confirmed%20by%20a%20parent.%20If%20it%20isn't%2C%20the%20user%20has%2090%20days%20to%20file%20a%20dispute%20before%20being%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20that%20allow%20minors%20access%20after%20being%20aware%20of%20their%20age%20could%20be%20responsible%20for%20up%20to%20%2450%2C000%20in%20penalties%20or%20fines%20per%20violation%20if%20the%20charges%20are%20found%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20pattern%20of%20knowing%20or%20reckless%20conduct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20can%20also%20sue%20companies%20on%20behalf%20of%20their%20child%20if%20the%20platform%20doesn't%20comply%20and%20take%20down%20the%20account%2C%20potentially%20receiving%20up%20to%20%2410%2C000%20in%20damages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPrivacy%20vs.%20protection%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20legislation%20is%20set%20to%20go%20into%20place%20by%20January%202025%2C%20Stacey%20Lee%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20%26amp%3B%20ethics%20at%20the%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Carey%20Business%20School%20said%20the%20bill%20will%20likely%20face%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20legal%20obstacles%26quot%3B%20related%20to%20First%20Amendment%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20said%20regulating%20social%20media%20has%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bhot-button%20political%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20these%20efforts%20are%20consistently%20met%20with%20constitutional%20hurdles%2C%20which%20DeSantis%20has%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill's%20effectiveness%20in%20preventing%20minors%20from%20accessing%20social%20media%20also%20remains%20questionable%2C%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegulating%20the%20digital%20landscape%20for%20minors%20without%20infringing%20on%20these%20principles%20presents%20a%20formidable%20challenge%20calling%20for%20thoughtful%20consideration%20and%20innovative%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20states%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Futah-governor-signs-law-restricting-teenagers-social-media-access-2023-3%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520law%252C%2520which%2520is%2520set%2Cinformation%2520from%2520a%2520minor%2527s%2520account.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20California%2C%20Utah%2C%20Ohio%2C%20and%20Arkansas%2C%20have%20been%20challenged%20by%20tech%20coalition%20NetChoice%20LLC%20for%20signing%20similar%20laws.%20Both%20California%20and%20Arkansas%20received%20preliminary%20injunctions%20and%20Ohio%20received%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20on%20its%20social%20media%20law%2C%20according%20to%20spokesperson%20Krista%20Chavez.%20The%20case%20in%20Utah%20hasn't%20had%20its%20hearing%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetChoice%20is%20a%20major%20coalition%20of%20social%20media%20platforms%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-cases-political-censorship-content-moderation-social-media-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopposing%20these%20restrictions%20and%20it%20includes%20TikTok%2C%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20X%20among%20others.%20NetChoice%20has%20cited%20privacy%20concerns%20in%20its%20reasoning%20against%20these%20kinds%20of%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChavez%20said%20NetChoice%20has%20repeatedly%20expressed%20constitutional%20concerns%20with%20HB3%20in%20public%20statements%2C%20testimony%2C%20and%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20Gov.%20DeSantis%20about%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetChoice%20Vice%20President%20%26amp%3B%20General%20Counsel%20Carl%20Szabo%20referred%20to%20HB3%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20policy%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESzabo%20said%20the%20bill%20poses%20a%20data%20risk%20because%20it%20forces%20users%20to%20hand%20over%20sensitive%20personal%20information%20to%20websites%20or%20lose%20their%20access%20to%20information%20channels.%20It%20also%20infringes%20on%20First%20Amendment%20rights%20to%20share%20and%20access%20online%20speech%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20disappointed%20to%20see%20Gov.%20DeSantis%20sign%20onto%20this%20route%2C%26quot%3B%20Szabo%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20better%20ways%20to%20keep%20Floridians%2C%20their%20families%2C%20and%20their%20data%20safe%20and%20secure%20online%20without%20violating%20their%20freedoms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAnother%20attempt%20at%20regulating%20social%20media%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeSantis%20voted%20against%20a%20more%20restrictive%20version%20of%20the%20bill%20that%20proposed%20banning%20social%20media%20for%20children%20under%2016%20and%20required%20proof%20of%20ID%20to%20join%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20governor%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGovRonDeSantis%2Fstatus%2F1763659319596224708%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bvetoed%20HB%201%20because%20the%20Legislature%20is%20about%20to%20produce%20a%20different%2C%20superior%20bill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20Florida%20governor%20has%20focused%20his%20legislation%20on%20protecting%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeSantis%20passed%20a%20bill%20last%20year%20that%20restricted%20children's%20use%20of%20cellphones%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20buried%20in%20those%20devices%20all%20day%20is%20not%20the%20best%20way%20to%20grow%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20DeSantis%20said%20at%20the%20signing%20ceremony.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20best%20way%20to%20get%20a%20good%20education.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20bill%20follows%20a%20series%20of%20legislative%20attempts%20from%20the%20government%20to%20place%20restrictions%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attempt%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-house-vote-results-uncertain-in-the-senate-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eban%20or%20force%20a%20sale%20of%20TikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20passed%20the%20House%20on%20March%2013%20with%20352%20votes%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20bill.%20It%20will%20next%20be%20voted%20on%20by%20the%20Senate%2C%20at%20which%20point%2C%20if%20it%20passes%2C%20it%20will%20end%20up%20on%20the%20desk%20of%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20said%20he'd%20sign%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-can-sue-soc