in%20India's%20history%2C%20like%20shooting%20a%20bullet%20with%20a%20bullet%20at%20a%20distance%20of%20nearly%20300%20km.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20day%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20India's%20defence%20scientists%20shot%20down%20a%20live%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)-made%20satellite%20and%20the%20country%20celebrated%20the%20unique%20'hit-to-kill'%20achievement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReliving%20that%20moment%2C%20Dr%20G%20Satheesh%20Reddy%2C%20former%20scientific%20advisor%20to%20the%20defence%20minister%20and%20the%20person%20who%20spearheaded%20the%20test%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAnti-satellite%20capability%20works%20as%20a%20deterrent%20in%20protecting%20India's%20space%20assets%2C%20and%20a%20test%20was%20conducted%20smoothly%20and%20secretly%20five%20years%20ago%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2027%2C%202019%2C%20scientists%20from%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20lay%20in%20patient%20wait%20as%20the%20Indian-made%20satellite%20Microsat-R%20came%20into%20the%20field%20of%20vision.%20A%20single%20missile%20was%20fired%20from%20the%20Dr%20APJ%20Abdul%20Kalam%20Island%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20and%2C%20less%20than%20three%20minutes%20later%2C%20the%20satellite%20was%20blown%20to%20pieces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECodenamed%20'Mission%20Shakti'%2C%20this%20was%20hailed%20as%20a%20big%20success%20since%20only%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%20had%20carried%20out%20anti-satellite%20weapons%20tests%20till%20then.%20The%20test%20was%20described%20as%20being%20akin%20to%20carrying%20out%20a%20surgical%20strike%20in%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESitting%20Ducks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20shot%20down%20a%20low-earth%20orbiting%20satellite%20using%20a%20kinetic%20weapon%20and%20demonstrated%20its%20capability%20of%20defending%20its%20own%20space%20assets%20and%20also%20destroying%20any%20satellites%20that%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20its%20vast%20constellation%20of%20over%2050%20satellites%20in%20which%20the%20country%20has%20invested%20more%20than%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20satellites%20were%2C%20till%20recently%2C%20the%20largest%20such%20constellation%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%20and%20these%20need%20to%20be%20protected%20very%20actively%20as%20they%20are%20sitting%20ducks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Speck%20In%20Space%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20address%20that%20day%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20did%20not%20confirm%20which%20satellite%20was%20shot%20down%20by%20DRDO.%20Subsequently%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20it%20was%20the%20satellite%20called%20Microsat-R%20which%20was%20launched%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%20283%20kilometres%20by%20the%20Polar%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle%20on%20January%2024%2C%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E'Mission%20Shakti'%20demonstrated%20that%20India%20can%20actively%20kill%20any%20satellite%20orbiting%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%20300%20kilometres%2C%20and%20the%20country%20has%20had%20the%20capability%20to%20conduct%20anti-satellite%20weapons%20tests%20for%20at%20least%20fifteen%20years%2C%20said%20a%20DRDO%20scientist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBringing%20down%20a%20satellite%20at%20that%20altitude%20is%20not%20easy%20since%20it%20would%20be%20travelling%20at%20a%20velocity%20of%20about%2028%2C080%20kilometres%20per%20hour%2C%20or%207.8%20kilometres%20per%20second%2C%20and%20targeting%20such%20a%20small%20speck%20-%20as%20the%20satellite%20would%20appear%20at%20that%20distance%20-%20is%20a%20big%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20later%20confirmed%20that%20India%20had%20used%20a%20new%20missile%20system%20named%20Prithvi%20Defence%20Vehicle%20Mark-II%2C%20which%20can%20target%20fast-moving%20satellites%20and%20bring%20them%20down.%20The%20missile%20was%2013%20metres%20long%20and%20weighed%20nearly%2020%20tonnes%2C%20but%20achieved%20pinpoint%20accuracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpace%20Debris%20Row%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20nations%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20worried%20that%20such%20a%20test%20would%20cause%20space%20debris%20that%20poses%20problems%20for%20other%20satellites.%20There%20was%20much%20criticism%20of%20the%20earlier%20Chinese%20anti-satellite%20weapons%20test%20since%20it%20had%20created%20hundreds%20of%20pieces%20of%20space%20debris.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20test%20generated%20270-300%20pieces%20of%20debris%2C%20but%20that%20was%20only%20a%20tiny%20proportion%20of%20millions%20of%20pieces%20floating%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20did%20India's%20satellite%20killer%20test%20cause%20debris%20that%20endangered%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20as%20was%20claimed%20by%20the%20then%20chief%20of%20NASA%20Jim%20Bridenstine%3F%20Dr%20G%20Madhavan%20Nair%2C%20former%20ISRO%20chief%2C%20had%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20test%20done%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%20300%20km%20may%20not%20leave%20space%20debris%20for%20too%20long%26quot%3B.%20And%20he%20stands%20vindicated%20as%20all%20debris%20has%20since%20disintegrated%20and%20burnt.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Evil'%20Eyes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWing%20Commander%20(Retd)%20Rakesh%20Sharma%2C%20India's%20only%20astronaut%20to%20have%20gone%20into%20space%2C%20said%20Mission%20Shakti%20gave%20India%20%26quot%3Bthe%20capability%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20'evil'%20eyes%20in%20space%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20'International%20Seminar%20on%20Aerospace%20Power%20in%20Future%20Conflicts'%20in%20New%20Delhi%20today%2C%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20VR%20Chaudhari%2C%20Chief%20of%20the%20Air%20Staff%2C%20Indian%20Air%20Force%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20evolution%20of%20aerospace%20power%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20matter%20of%20technological%20prowess%20but%20also%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20ingenuity%20and%20adaptability%20of%20human%20innovation%20in%20the%20face%20of%20emerging%20threats%20and%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpace%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20critical%20domain%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20military%20operations%2C%20wherein%20seamless%20communication%2C%20navigation%20and%20surveillance%20capabilities%20would%20enhance%20the%20survivability%20of%20modern%20military%20forces.%20As%20nations%20increasingly%20rely%20on%20space-based%20assets%20for%20building%20strategic%20advantage%2C%20militarisation%20and%20weaponisation%20of%20space%20has%20become%20an%20inevitable%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Arms%20Race%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20had%20asserted%20in%202019%3A%20%26quot%3BIndia%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20entering%20into%20an%20arms%20race%20in%20outer%20space.%20We%20have%20always%20maintained%20that%20space%20must%20be%20used%20only%20for%20peaceful%20purposes.%20We%20are%20against%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20outer%20space%20and%20support%20international%20efforts%20to%20reinforce%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20space-based%20assets.%20India%20believes%20that%20outer%20space%20is%20the%20common%20heritage%20of%20humankind%20and%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20all%20space-faring%20nations%20to%20preserve%20and%20promote%20the%20benefits%20flowing%20from%20advances%20made%20in%20space%20technology%20and%20its%20applications%20for%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Ravi%20Gupta%2C%20a%20former%20scientist%20with%20DRDO%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20space%20assets%20and%20defence%20against%20strategic%20weapons%2C%20deterrence%20is%20the%20best%20defence.%20Mission%20Shakti%20gave%20Bharat's%20deterrence%20capabilities%20a%20quantum%20jump%2C%20and%20Divyastra%20(the%20Agni%205-Multiple%20Independently%20targetable%20Reentry%20Vehicles%20test%20of%20March%2011%2C%202024)%20was%20yet%20another%20quantum%20jump.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20scientific%20advisor%20Reddy%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMission%20Shakti%20was%20a%20huge%20technological%20milestone%20achieved%20by%20India.%20The%20test%20was%20conducted%20leaving%20minimal%20debris%20behind%20and%20today%20no%20debris%20exists%20in%20space%20arising%20out%20of%20the%20mission.%20On%20the%20directions%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20test%20was%20done%20to%20show%20the%20technological%20capability%20to%20the%20world.'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20five%20years%20since%20then%2C%20and%20India%20has%20not%20tested%20an%20anti-satellite%20weapon%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711544280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fpt73skbo_isro-antisatellite-missile-test_625x300_27_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-celestial-encounter-when-india-shot-down-its-own-satellite-5321235%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20March%2027%2C%202019%2C%20India's%20defence%20scientists%20shot%20down%20a%20live%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)-made%20satellite%20and%20the%20country%20celebrated%20the%20unique%20'hit-to-kill'%20achievement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-celestial-encounter-when-india-shot-down-its-own-satellite-5321235%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disney%20Activist%20Investor%20Nelson%20Peltz%E2%80%99s%20Trian%20Wins%20Endorsement%20for%20Board%20Candidates%20From%20Advisory%20Firm%20Egan-Jones%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711544270000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FDisneyland-Mickey-Mouse.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235953262%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nelson%20Peltz%20has%20received%20the%20backing%20of%20another%20investor-advisory%20fi