0prepare%20for%20the%20%2420%20minimum%20wage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPizza%20Hut%20franchisees%20plan%20to%20lay%20off%20around%201%2C200%20workers%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERestaurants%20are%20also%20raising%20prices%20to%20offset%20wages%3B%20some%20are%20worried%20about%20spooking%20diners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFast-food%20restaurants%20in%20California%20are%20laying%20off%20hundreds%20of%20workers%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20costs%20as%20they%20prepare%20for%20the%20state's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-20-dollar-fast-food-wage-restaurant-prices-jobs-workers-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2420%20minimum%20wage%20for%20fast-food%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20comes%20into%20force%20in%20April%2C%20a%20new%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fhospitality%2Fcalifornia-restaurants-cut-jobs-as-fast-food-wages-set-to-rise-eb5ddaaa%3Fmod%3Dbusiness_lead_story%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-pizza-hut-lays-off-delivery-drivers-amid-new-wage-law-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwo%20franchisees%20for%20Pizza%20Hut%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20restaurants%20across%20various%20counties%20in%20California%2C%20have%20said%20they'd%20lay%20off%20around%201%2C200%20workers%20as%20they%20scrap%20delivery-driver%20roles%20to%20rely%20on%20third-party%20delivery%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthern%20California%20Pizza%20Company%2C%20a%20Pizza%20Hut%20franchisee%2C%20said%20it%20planned%20to%20lay%20off%20nearly%20850%20workers%20in%20February%2C%20according%20to%20filings%20made%20under%20California's%20Worker%20Adjustment%20and%20Retraining%20Notification%20Act%20in%20December%20and%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20another%20Pizza%20Hut%20franchisee%2C%20PacPizza%2C%20and%20its%20affiliates%20filed%20plans%20to%20lay%20off%20more%20than%20350%20workers%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20February%2C%20Excalibur%20Pizza%20LLC%2C%20a%20Round%20Table%20Pizza%20franchisee%2C%20said%20it%20planned%20to%20lay%20off%2070%20workers%20in%20April%2C%20WARN%20Act%20filings%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERound%20Table%20Pizza%2C%20which%20has%20more%20than%20400%20locations%20in%20the%20US%2C%20mainly%20along%20the%20West%20Coast%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20employees%20being%20laid%20off%20were%20delivery%20drivers%20and%20that%20Excalibur%20was%20moving%20to%20third-party%20delivery%20services.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20saw%20the%20layoffs%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btransfer%20of%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20more%20workers%20required%20at%20third-party%20delivery%20services%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20said%2C%20delivery%20service%20fees%20may%20increase%2C%20and%20the%20customer%20will%20most%20likely%20see%20even%20higher%20prices%20as%20a%20result%20of%20this%20ongoing%20shift%2C%26quot%3B%20Round%20Table%20Pizza's%20statement%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20reality%20of%20today's%20restaurants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20fast-food%20franchisee%20has%20even%20roped%20in%20his%2073-year-old%20parents%20to%20help%20out%20after%20cutting%20staff.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Johnson%2C%20who%20owns%2010%20Auntie%20Anne's%20and%20Cinnabon%20locations%20in%20California%2C%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20the%20new%20law%20would%20have%20otherwise%20cost%20him%20an%20extra%20%24470%2C000%20in%20labor%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFranchisees%20are%20worried%20about%20higher%20prices%20spooking%20diners%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20is%20raising%20the%20state's%20minimum%20wage%20for%20workers%20at%20limited-service%20restaurants%20to%20%2420%20an%20hour%20from%20April%201%20%E2%80%94%2025%25%20higher%20than%20its%20general%20minimum%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20only%20applies%20to%20chains%20with%20at%20least%2060%20locations