C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-remains-polio-free-all-vaccines-in-government-immunisation-safe-unicef-who-1930498%5C%22%3E23%20arduous%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20nationwide%20campaigns%20led%20by%20legions%20of%20volunteers%20and%20healthcare%20workers%20who%20immunised%20millions%20of%20children%20against%20polio%20in%20the%20far%20reaches%20of%20the%20country%2C%20India%20has%20defied%20these%20bleak%20expectations.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20last%20poliovirus%20case%20was%20reported%20in%20Howrah%20district%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20in%202011%2C%20and%20three%20years%20later%2C%20India%20was%20officially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftelangana-news%2Fpolio-virus-resurfaces-in-hyderabad-after-5-years-1419179%5C%22%3Ecertified%20polio-free%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20the%20South-East%20Asia%20Region%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20marks%20a%20decade%20of%20a%20polio-free%20India%20-%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20profound%20public%20health%20achievements%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Journey%20to%20End%20Polio%3A%20A%20Battle%20of%20Sheer%20Scale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hard-won%20fight%20of%20epic%20proportions%2C%20the%20effort%20to%20end%20polio%20in%20India%20was%20beset%20with%20overwhelming%20challenges.%20From%20misinformation%20and%20myths%20about%20the%20polio%20vaccine%20to%20high%20population%20density%2C%20poor%20sanitation%2C%20and%20inaccessible%20terrains%2C%20the%20country%20overcame%20what%20many%20considered%20impossible.%20As%20recently%20as%202009%2C%20India%20was%20a%20polio%20hotspot%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20all%20polio%20cases%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20India%20responded%20with%20resilience%2C%20launching%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20comprehensive%20vaccination%20campaigns%20in%20history.%20Through%20the%20pulse%20polio%20immunisation%20programme%2C%20the%20government%20of%20India%20conducted%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20national%20immunisation%20days%20(NIDs)%20and%20sub-national%20immunisation%20days%20(SNIDS)%2C%20where%20every%20child%20up%20to%20age%20five%20received%20the%20polio%20vaccine.%20Additionally%2C%20complementary%20health%20services%2C%20such%20as%20Vitamin%20A%20drops%2C%20were%20included%20to%20protect%20children%20further%20and%20engage%20parents%20and%20families%20in%20support%20of%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaccinating%20millions%20of%20children%20was%20an%20arduous%20task%20for%20many%20reasons%2C%20one%20of%20which%20was%20weather.%20During%20seasonal%20floods%20in%20Bihar%2C%20thousands%20of%20children%20were%20trapped%20in%20crowded%20and%20unsanitary%20makeshift%20camps%20on%20small%20islands%20surrounded%20by%20floodwaters.%20Although%20this%20state%20previously%20reported%20the%20second-highest%20number%20of%20polio%20cases%20in%20the%20country%20in%202006%20and%202007%2C%20healthcare%20workers%20were%20undeterred%2C%20reaching%20the%20stranded%20children%20by%20boat%20to%20ensure%20they%20were%20vaccinated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemote%20terrain%20was%20also%20an%20obstacle%2C%20as%20was%20the%20case%20in%20the%20hills%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Rajasthan.%20Due%20to%20their%20nomadic%20lifestyles%2C%20migrant%20populations%20were%20difficult%20to%20reach.%20This%20remained%20an%20ever-present%20concern%2C%20as%20children%20within%20these%20communities%20were%20consistently%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20either%20left%20out%20of%20immunisation%20efforts%20entirely%20or%20of%20not%20receiving%20the%20required%20total%20doses%20of%20the%20polio%20vaccine.%3Cbr%3E%5CnHealthcare%20workers%20trekked%20for%20hours%2C%20and%20some%20rode%20camels%20to%20reach%20children%20with%20the%20polio%20vaccine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20thoughtfully%20collaborated%20with%20communities%20that%20held%20fears%20about%20the%20vaccine.%20With%20the%20support%20and%20encouragement%20of%20local%20political%20and%20religious%20leaders%20and%20celebrities%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20educate%20parents%20about%20the%20vaccine%20and%20calm%20their%20fears%20enough%20to%20allow%20their%20children%20to%20be%20immunised%20against%20polio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20pulse%20polio%20programme%20was%20backed%20by%20India's%20multi-pronged%20surveillance%20and%20environmental%20surveillance%20network%2C%20a%20highly%20sensitive%20laboratory-backed%20system%20that%20monitored%20the%20circulation%20of%20poliovirus%20strains%20in%20stools%20of%20paralytic%20cases%20and%20sewage%20samples.%20The%20network%20enrolled%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20health%20facilities%20across%20the%20country%20to%20report%20paralytic%20cases%20to%20help%20limit%20the%20chances%20of%20an%20outbreak.%20Through%20real-time%2C%20credible%20data%2C%20the%20nation%20adapted%20its%20immunisation%20strategies%20to%20focus%20on%20high-risk%20areas%20and%20vulnerable%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolio%20immunisation%20campaigns%20were%20a%20nationwide%20mission%20that%20spanned%20decades.%20Millions%20of%20vaccinators%20were%20united%20by%20a%20singular%20goal%3A%20to%20protect%20every%20child%20from%20polio%2C%20transcending%20geographical%2C%20logistical%2C%20and%20cultural%20barriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20today%2C%20over%20170%20million%20children%20are%20immunised%20during%20NIDs%2C%20and%2077%20million%20are%20immunised%20during%20SNIDs%20every%20year%20to%20ensure%20India%20remains%20polio-free%2C%20thus%20preventing%20millions%20of%20children%20from%20possible%20paralysis%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECollaboration%3A%20Key%20To%20The%20Endgame%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnding%20polio%20in%20India%20was%20achieved%20through%20the%20mass%20development%20and%20distribution%20of%20billions%20of%20vaccines%20-%20all%20made%20possible%20through%20a%20strategic%20alliance%20with%20the%20Global%20Polio%20Eradication%20Initiative%20(GPEI)%20and%20its%20partners%20-%20the%20WHO%2C%20Rotary%2C%20the%20US%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20Children's%20Fund%20(UNICEF)%2C%20Bill%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20Gavi%2C%20the%20Vaccine%20Alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20polio%20has%20been%20eliminated%20in%20India%2C%20the%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(NFHS-5)%20revealed%20that%20only%2077%25%20of%20children%20(aged%20one-two%20years)%20received%20all%20basic%20vaccinations.%20While%2092%25%20of%20children%20(aged%20one-two%20years)%20received%20the%20first%20dose%20of%20the%20polio%20vaccine%2C%20only%2081%25%20received%20the%20last%20dose.%20Additionally%2C%204%25%20of%20this%20demographic%20received%20zero%20vaccinations.%20Given%20India's%20proximity%20to%20the%20remaining%20two%20polio-endemic%20countries%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20social%20and%20environmental%20factors%2C%20the%20country%20cannot%20let%20its%20guard%20down.%20It%20must%20continue%20with%20its%20polio%20vaccination%20activities%20to%20sustain%20population%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Rotary%20and%20its%20partners%2C%20the%20incidence%20of%20wild%20polio%20globally%20has%20been%20reduced%20by%2099.%25%2C%20and%20most%20of%20the%20world's%20children%20now%20live%20in%20polio-free%20countries.%20To%20ensure%20every%20child%20is%20protected%20from%20polio%2C%20all%20parties%20must%20remain%20united%20behind%20this%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20robust%20vaccination%20and%20monitoring%20efforts%2C%20the%20world%20can%20finally%20bid%20farewell%20to%20polio%20and%20create%20a%20new%20future%20where%20no%20child%20will%20face%20the%20threat%20of%20this%20disease.%20The%20journey%20continues%2C%20fuelled%20by%20optimism%2C%20determination%2C%20and%20the%20shared%20belief%20that%20a%20polio-free%20world%20is%20not%20just%20a%20dream%20but%20an%20achievable%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20