%3EOld%20field%2C%20new%20crop%2C%20huge%20success%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20from%20an%20agricultural%20background%2C%20Kanchan%20turned%20to%20farming%20soon%20after%20her%20marriage.%20Alongside%20cultivating%20vegetables%2C%20wheat%2C%20and%20maize%2C%20the%20BA%20graduate%20sowed%20turmeric%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20programme%20on%20television%20that%20showcased%20the%20advantages%20of%20taking%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F274975%2Fdivine-foods-helps-organic-turmeric-farmers-earn-double-sell-to-us-uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturmeric%20farming%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20learn%20more%20about%20it%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20nearby%20KVK%20(Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra)%20and%20undertook%20a%20training%20programme%20of%20seven%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKanchan%20opted%20for%20the%20Sangli%20variety%20of%20turmeric%20which%20has%20high%20curcumin%20turmeric%20and%20is%20often%20used%20for%20medicinal%20purposes.%20In%20addition%20to%20its%20deep-orange%20colour%20and%20rich%20aroma%2C%20Kanchan%20says%2C%20this%20variety%20produces%20big%20roots%20compared%20to%20other%20indigenous%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20procured%20eight%20quintals%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20haldi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(seed)%20from%20KVK%20at%20Rs%2040%20per%20kg.%20%E2%80%9CThereafter%2C%20we%20started%20tilling%20the%20farmland%20to%20remove%20weeds%20and%20reduce%20the%20soil%20compaction%20%5Brelieve%20the%20tightness%20of%20soil%5D%2C%20and%20level%20the%20soil.%20After%20seedbed%20preparation%2C%20we%20added%20four%20trolleys%20(1%20trolley%20comprises%2040%20quintals)%20of%20cow%20dung%20in%20the%20soil.%20We%20then%20sowed%20germinated%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20haldi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20the%20beds.%20The%20process%20is%20similar%20to%20sowing%20any%20tuber%20crop%20like%20potatoes%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kanchan%20claims%20she%20is%20the%20first%20such%20farmer%20to%20practice%20turmeric%20farming%20in%20this%20region.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345840%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKanchan%20claims%20she%20is%20the%20first%20such%20farmer%20to%20practice%20turmeric%20farming%20in%20this%20region.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20turmeric%20farming%2C%20the%20soil%20is%20usually%20mounded%20around%20the%20base%20of%20a%20plant%20to%20get%20large%20rhizomes.%20At%20first%2C%20Kanchan%20says%20she%20did%20not%20know%20the%20right%20time%20to%20earth%20up%20the%20plant.%20She%20later%20learned%20that%20it%20was%20done%20a%20month%20after%20planting%20the%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20sowing%20period%20is%20between%20June%20and%20July%2C%20the%20crop%20is%20ready%20for%20harvest%20by%20February-end.%20She%20points%20out%20that%20it%20is%20very%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20kind%20of%20soil%20used%20for%20cultivation.%20%E2%80%9COur%20region%20is%20famous%20for%20black%20soil%20that%20is%20suitable%20for%20wheat%20cultivation.%20However%2C%20a%20well-drained%20sandy%20loam%20soil%20rich%20in%20humus%20content%20works%20well%20for%20growing%20turmeric%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20black%20soil%20is%20soft%20when%20wet%20but%20forms%20hard%20blocks%20when%20it%20gets%20dry.%20So%2C%20we%20need%20a%20sandy%20loamy%20solid%20that%20is%20well-drained.%20In%20our%20district%2C%20only%20a%20few%20blocks%20including%20our%20Kesla%20block%20have%20such%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20required%20for%20boosting%20turmeric%20growth%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20use%20cow%20dung%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejeevamrut%20%3C%2Fem%3E(liquid%20organic%20manure)%20to%20boost%20the%20fertility%20of%20the%20soil.%20Besides%2C%20as%20turmeric%20in%20itself%20is%20antiseptic%20and%20herbal%2C%20there%20are%20fewer%20chances%20of%20pest%20attack.%20Even%20if%20pests%20attack%20the%20crop%2C%20we%20use%20Trichoderma%20biopesticides%20to%20control%20the%20attack%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20careful%20of%20growing%20a%20new%20crop%2C%20Kanchan%20sowed%20and%20used%20only%20an%20acre%20of%20land%20to%20sow%20eight%20quintals%20of%20turmeric%20root.%20After%20eight%20months%2C%20she%20harvested%20bumper%20produce%20of%20100%20quintals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Last%20year%2C%20Kanchan%20got%20a%20bountiful%20harvest%20of%20400%20quintals%2C%20earning%20an%20income%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F